Religion in [[Cuba]] is a guaranteed right, meaning that [[Buddhism]] can be practiced in the country. Traditionally, most religious people in [[Cuba]] practice [[Christianity]] or other [[Indigenous religion]]s. Some Buddhist figures have traveled to the country in the past, no big problems have arisen to this point. Originally brought by the Chinese immigrants, it is now practiced in communities monitored overseas. The number of practitioners is small.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.sgi.org/people-and-perspectives/Buddhism-in-Cuba.html|title=Buddhism in Cuba {{!}} Soka Gakkai International (SGI)|last=(SGI)|first=Soka Gakkai International|website=www.sgi.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref>

