In [[Aztec mythology]] '''Huitztlampaehecatl''' ({{IPA-nah|witstɬaːmpaeʔekatɬ}}) is the god of the [[South wind]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario de Mitología Nahua|editor=Biblioteca Porrúa. Imprenta del Museo Nacional de Arqueología, Historia y Etnología|authorlink=Cecilio Agustín Robelo|language=Spanish|year=1905|location=México|pages=168, 169|isbn=978-9684327955}}</ref> His brothers are [[Cihuatecayotl]], [[Tlalocayotl]], and [[Mictlanpachecatl]], who personify the winds from the [[West wind|west]], [[East wind|east]], and [[North wind|north]] respectively.<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario de Mitología Nahua|editor=Biblioteca Porrúa. Imprenta del Museo Nacional de Arqueología, Historia y Etnología|authorlink=Cecilio Agustín Robelo|language=Spanish|year=1905|location=México|pages=168, 169|isbn=978-9684327955}}</ref>
