'''Jorge Ardila Serrano''' (September 17, 1927, Zapatoca, Colombia &ndash; October 12, 2010, Girardot, Colombia) was the [[Roman Catholic]] bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Girardot]], [[Colombia]].

Ordained to the priesthood on October 17, 1948, he was appointed [[auxiliary bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bogota]] on October 27, 1980, and was ordained on November 30, 1980. In 1988, he was appointed bishop of the Girardot Diocese retiring in 2001.<ref>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|bardser|Bishop Jorge Ardila Serrano|21 January 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://prezi.com/1b2etvqycsb3/ Copy of MONSEÑOR JORGE ARDILA SERRANO, SIGNO DEL AMOR DE DIOS PARA S by Alvaro Gaitan on Prezi]</ref>

